	"description": "One of the key factors that differentiates HTML 5 from its predecessors is the\nintroduction of semantic tags. \n\nSemantic tags add real meaning to the webpage and make it easy for humans, and\nsearch engines, to differentiate between different parts of the website. \n\nTo a certain extent, it affects the SEO of a webpage, too. \n\nSo to reap the benefits, you should know the HTML5 tags you can use to enhance\nyour website. \n\nThere are some very useful but little-known HTML5 tags that can come in handy,",
